    {
      "id": "PopularPost121494",
      "post_content": "@achilles: [Wings of Aesthir](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wings of Aesthir) costs ![White](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=W&type=symbol) ![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol), which means a comparable blue-only cost would be something like ![2](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=2&type=symbol) ![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol). Since [Flight](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flight) is only ![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol), you are getting the first-strike-while-blocking for about as cheap as you could get it without making the card strictly better than Flight.   \n  \nIt also makes sense that you (and not any player) have snow lands out to trigger the ability. There's supposed to be some tension between the advantages and disadvantages of using snow lands, and this is supposed to be an advantage. However, if there's a good chance my non-island snow lands help someone else's blue deck be better, I probably would be reluctant to run them. By removing the enemy's lands from consideration, the ability can be seen universally as a benefit to running snow lands when constructing a deck.  \n  \nThe condition on blocking is a bit too restrictive for the cost, though. I'm pretty sure that's for flavor reasons. (\"Hey, why does your guy benefit f... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "longwinded",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost121494\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">@achilles: <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wings of Aesthir\">Wings of Aesthir</a> costs <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"White\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=W&amp;type=symbol\"/> <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Blue\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=U&amp;type=symbol\"/>, which means a comparable blue-only cost would be something like <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"2\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=2&amp;type=symbol\"/> <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Blue\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=U&amp;type=symbol\"/>. Since <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flight\">Flight</a> is only <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Blue\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=U&amp;type=symbol\"/>, you are getting the first-strike-while-blocking for about as cheap as you could get it without making the card strictly better than Flight. <br/><br/>It also makes sense that you (and not any player) have snow lands out to trigger the ability. There's supposed to be some tension between the advantages and disadvantages of using snow lands, and this is supposed to be an advantage. However, if there's a good chance my non-island snow lands help someone else's blue deck be better, I probably would be reluctant to run them. By removing the enemy's lands from consideration, the ability can be seen universally as a benefit to running snow lands when constructing a deck.<br/><br/>The condition on blocking is a bit too restrictive for the cost, though. I'm pretty sure that's for flavor reasons. (\"Hey, why does your guy benefit f... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 121494)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: <a class=\"postedByLink\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"PostedBy40319\">longwinded</a>\r\n                                (12/11/2010 8:31:39 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.gif\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.gif\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.gif\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.gif\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.gif\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.gif\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.gif\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.gif\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.gif\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.gif\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clea